1
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,000
=Our Days=

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,720
(Adapted from Lang Lang's original novel
"The Prime of the Goddess")

3
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:38,160
=Episode 4=

4
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:40,519
If you don't move, I'll post
your pictures on my WeChat Moments

5
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:41,859
so that you can be happy about it.

6
00:02:01,119 --> 00:02:03,340
You must be bored out of your mind.
That's no fun.

7
00:02:04,839 --> 00:02:05,939
Do you need to resort to that?

8
00:02:07,359 --> 00:02:08,939
He must be sick in the head.

9
00:02:23,287 --> 00:02:24,508
Mr. Gao Ping.

10
00:02:24,887 --> 00:02:27,027
Can we swap our car today?

11
00:02:27,308 --> 00:02:29,166
Mine is out of gas.
And, I have no time to refill it.

12
00:02:29,167 --> 00:02:30,587
Can you refill it for me this afternoon?

13
00:02:30,808 --> 00:02:32,027
No problem. Go ahead.

14
00:02:35,287 --> 00:02:36,228
Sorry.

15
00:02:37,047 --> 00:02:37,886
I cannot go back

16
00:02:37,887 --> 00:02:39,067
with you today.

17
00:02:39,368 --> 00:02:40,247
I need to finish this

18
00:02:40,248 --> 00:02:41,307
by 3 P.M.

19
00:02:41,968 --> 00:02:43,347
It's fine. You can go ahead.

20
00:02:44,208 --> 00:02:46,166
They have a swimming session at 5 P.M.

21
00:02:46,167 --> 00:02:47,027
Don't forget.

22
00:02:49,447 --> 00:02:50,127
Goodbye.

23
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:50,867
Goodbye.

24
00:03:23,287 --> 00:03:24,788
What are you doing here?

25
00:03:25,868 --> 00:03:27,600
Are you afraid
that I'll see your massage device?

26
00:03:29,047 --> 00:03:30,788
Didn't you say you already
gave it to someone else?

27
00:03:31,488 --> 00:03:32,907
It's a critical time for you

28
00:03:32,968 --> 00:03:34,948
to remain in the hospital now.

29
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:37,446
Can you let go of

30
00:03:37,447 --> 00:03:39,067
some of that arrogance of yours?

31
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:41,147
It's pointless for you
to be professional alone.

32
00:03:41,167 --> 00:03:43,228
Don't you think you have to establish
some connections too?

33
00:03:43,567 --> 00:03:44,788
I'm not trying to be arrogant here.

34
00:03:45,907 --> 00:03:47,067
I did try to deliver it to her.

35
00:03:47,528 --> 00:03:48,687
But Dayuan also bought

36
00:03:48,688 --> 00:03:50,407
a 6,000 yuan chair
for Ms. Yuan at the same time.

37
00:03:50,408 --> 00:03:51,228
I was

38
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:53,347
too embarrassed to give it to her.

39
00:03:53,648 --> 00:03:55,367
It's the thought that counts

40
00:03:55,368 --> 00:03:56,988
when a student gives his teacher a gift.

41
00:03:57,767 --> 00:03:59,388
It has nothing to do with the price.

42
00:03:59,408 --> 00:04:00,446
Isn't it great?

43
00:04:00,447 --> 00:04:01,927
He's gifting her a chair while
you're gifting her a massage device.

44
00:04:01,928 --> 00:04:03,240
At least the gifts aren't the same.

45
00:04:07,368 --> 00:04:08,747
What will you do, then?

46
00:04:09,968 --> 00:04:11,307
Will you buy something more expensive?

47
00:04:12,887 --> 00:04:15,147
I don't have money for that.
I only have a tiny bit of allowance.

48
00:04:16,968 --> 00:04:18,347
What do you mean by that?

49
00:04:19,688 --> 00:04:21,487
We've been living together
for almost five years now.

50
00:04:21,488 --> 00:04:23,307
Now, you're trying
to differentiate between us, huh?

51
00:04:25,168 --> 00:04:27,247
There's no need for that.
I didn't contribute anything.

52
00:04:27,248 --> 00:04:28,908
You're the one sustaining the family.

53
00:04:30,488 --> 00:04:32,307
You'll graduate soon, right?

54
00:04:32,767 --> 00:04:35,067
By then, you can give me your wage.

55
00:04:38,748 --> 00:04:40,588
You can't do anything
with that measly wage of mine.

56
00:04:43,168 --> 00:04:44,148
So?

57
00:04:45,488 --> 00:04:47,566
I know you don't mind.
But you should consider my feelings.

58
00:04:47,567 --> 00:04:50,588
I can't just spend your money all the time
without feeling guilty, you know?

59
00:04:50,767 --> 00:04:52,006
Isn't this how we've divided things

60
00:04:52,007 --> 00:04:53,827
in our family all along?

61
00:04:54,447 --> 00:04:55,548
What's wrong?

62
00:04:59,288 --> 00:05:01,228
Did my words hurt you again?

63
00:05:01,688 --> 00:05:02,507
That's not it.

64
00:05:07,128 --> 00:05:08,387
You can proceed with your thesis.

65
00:05:09,307 --> 00:05:10,947
I'll deliver your massage device
to Mom and Dad.

66
00:05:27,248 --> 00:05:28,067
Mom.

67
00:05:28,327 --> 00:05:29,267
Have you eaten?

68
00:05:30,007 --> 00:05:32,228
Which meal do you mean?
Look at the time.

69
00:05:35,288 --> 00:05:36,267
Qian, look.

70
00:05:38,688 --> 00:05:39,788
Did you dye your hair?

71
00:05:40,248 --> 00:05:41,006
Why did you...

72
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:41,907
Lower your volume.

73
00:05:41,907 --> 00:05:43,167
Why did you only dye such a small part?

74
00:05:43,168 --> 00:05:44,966
I dare not go overboard.
Your father didn't like it.

75
00:05:44,967 --> 00:05:46,788
I told your aunt
to dye my hair in secret.

76
00:05:46,887 --> 00:05:48,428
- It looks nice, right?
- Yeah.

77
00:05:48,488 --> 00:05:49,960
If I must say, you should dye all of it.

78
00:05:50,048 --> 00:05:50,867
Xiang Qian.

79
00:05:50,928 --> 00:05:52,148
Why are you only back now?

80
00:05:52,748 --> 00:05:54,607
Look at the time.
Aren't we having dinner at 6 P.M.?

81
00:05:54,608 --> 00:05:57,187
Look at the time? I have to prepare dinner
in advance, you know?

82
00:05:58,007 --> 00:05:58,966
- Fine.
- What's wrong with your mother?

83
00:05:58,967 --> 00:05:59,526
It's nothing.

84
00:05:59,527 --> 00:06:01,526
- Do you have a lice problem?
- That's not it. Let me help you out.

85
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:03,028
I'm fine. Everything's fine.

86
00:06:16,048 --> 00:06:16,827
Dad.

87
00:06:17,647 --> 00:06:19,086
Are you celebrating Chinese New Year?

88
00:06:19,087 --> 00:06:21,080
Didn't you say you were going
to prepare some simple dishes?

89
00:06:21,407 --> 00:06:22,526
These are the simple dishes

90
00:06:22,527 --> 00:06:23,788
we always prepare.

91
00:06:24,207 --> 00:06:25,326
You're quite hilarious, huh?

92
00:06:25,327 --> 00:06:26,326
Do you and Mom have them

93
00:06:26,327 --> 00:06:27,627
at home every day?

94
00:06:27,808 --> 00:06:28,807
If so, I'm sure you guys

95
00:06:28,808 --> 00:06:30,387
have to visit the hospital every day.

96
00:06:32,447 --> 00:06:33,827
It's not terrible.

97
00:06:33,928 --> 00:06:35,747
You guys grew up eating them, you know?

98
00:06:35,928 --> 00:06:36,446
Come.

99
00:06:36,447 --> 00:06:37,788
Grab me the scissors.

100
00:06:38,967 --> 00:06:39,707
Alright.

101
00:06:41,688 --> 00:06:43,028
By the way, Xiang Qian,

102
00:06:43,728 --> 00:06:47,006
I've gotten a thorough understanding

103
00:06:47,007 --> 00:06:49,108
of Jiang Hongbin's situation lately.

104
00:06:49,808 --> 00:06:51,028
What have you understood?

105
00:06:52,087 --> 00:06:53,047
I've read all reports

106
00:06:53,048 --> 00:06:54,267
that were related to him.

107
00:06:54,367 --> 00:06:55,627
I won't talk about the good ones.

108
00:06:56,368 --> 00:06:57,747
But some situations

109
00:06:57,967 --> 00:07:00,108
require a deeper understanding.

110
00:07:00,767 --> 00:07:02,067
It's all in my mind now.

111
00:07:03,007 --> 00:07:04,468
We have to act accordingly

112
00:07:05,048 --> 00:07:07,127
during the meal.

113
00:07:07,128 --> 00:07:08,428
We must make sure

114
00:07:08,887 --> 00:07:10,187
that each point is implemented.

115
00:07:16,207 --> 00:07:17,788
Monthly wage,

116
00:07:18,207 --> 00:07:19,947
and units in possession?

117
00:07:20,368 --> 00:07:20,807
Units?

118
00:07:20,808 --> 00:07:21,927
He builds houses for a living.

119
00:07:21,928 --> 00:07:23,607
How could he remember
how many units he has?

120
00:07:23,608 --> 00:07:24,947
That'll depend on

121
00:07:25,087 --> 00:07:26,588
a drinking session.

122
00:07:26,967 --> 00:07:27,947
Don't you agree?

123
00:07:28,647 --> 00:07:29,526
We'll be brave enough

124
00:07:29,527 --> 00:07:30,747
to ask him when we're drunk.

125
00:07:31,087 --> 00:07:32,127
And, he'll answer everything

126
00:07:32,128 --> 00:07:33,588
when he's drunk.

127
00:07:34,248 --> 00:07:36,788
We must drink well today.

128
00:07:36,928 --> 00:07:39,548
You must remember to stay sober.

129
00:07:40,288 --> 00:07:42,588
You must record his answers, okay?

130
00:07:44,488 --> 00:07:45,446
Understood?

131
00:07:45,447 --> 00:07:46,446
Understood.

132
00:07:46,447 --> 00:07:48,247
I'll obey your command.

133
00:07:48,248 --> 00:07:49,287
You even want to know about

134
00:07:49,288 --> 00:07:50,367
his monthly expenditures?

135
00:07:50,368 --> 00:07:51,908
What has this got to do with you?

136
00:07:53,087 --> 00:07:54,788
I'll go and find Mom. I'll get changed first.

137
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:55,988
I'll help you out later.

138
00:08:03,728 --> 00:08:04,047
Mom.

139
00:08:04,048 --> 00:08:05,428
Why isn't Xiang Zhong back yet?

140
00:08:07,248 --> 00:08:09,067
Your father argued with her.

141
00:08:09,288 --> 00:08:11,387
She didn't heed his advice.
She left after that.

142
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:13,727
Why does Dad like

143
00:08:13,728 --> 00:08:15,588
to provoke Xiang Zhong all the time?

144
00:08:16,848 --> 00:08:17,668
Say,

145
00:08:17,887 --> 00:08:19,588
is one bottle enough?

146
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:20,766
Don't talk to me.

147
00:08:20,767 --> 00:08:21,867
Let me take a picture first.

148
00:08:23,207 --> 00:08:24,627
Dad, Mom, Qian.

149
00:08:24,848 --> 00:08:25,668
Xiang Nan?

150
00:08:27,168 --> 00:08:27,947
Xiang Nan,

151
00:08:28,728 --> 00:08:30,148
why are you back alone?

152
00:08:30,887 --> 00:08:32,086
Jiang said

153
00:08:32,087 --> 00:08:33,526
he had a sudden meeting to attend.

154
00:08:33,527 --> 00:08:35,827
He told me to return first.
He'll come by himself later.

155
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:38,847
Today's an important gathering,
you know?

156
00:08:38,848 --> 00:08:40,087
How could he busy

157
00:08:40,088 --> 00:08:41,067
with something else?

158
00:08:42,167 --> 00:08:42,827
He...

159
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:44,247
He's a business owner.

160
00:08:44,248 --> 00:08:45,908
I can understand why he's busy.

161
00:08:46,647 --> 00:08:47,748
Can you?

162
00:08:48,007 --> 00:08:48,947
I can.

163
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:51,286
It's fine as long as
you can understand it.

164
00:08:51,287 --> 00:08:52,227
Where's Zhong?

165
00:08:52,328 --> 00:08:53,227
You can ask your father.

166
00:08:53,767 --> 00:08:54,908
Dad, where's Zhong?

167
00:08:55,807 --> 00:08:56,847
It doesn't matter if Zhong

168
00:08:56,848 --> 00:08:57,748
returns or not.

169
00:08:58,128 --> 00:08:59,668
She has a hard time with everyone.

170
00:08:59,728 --> 00:09:01,028
She spoils our mood when she's back.

171
00:09:01,807 --> 00:09:03,788
I wouldn't return either

172
00:09:03,968 --> 00:09:04,947
if I heard that.

173
00:09:05,208 --> 00:09:06,806
Aren't I just stating facts?

174
00:09:06,807 --> 00:09:07,847
What about this? I'll call her

175
00:09:07,848 --> 00:09:08,827
and ask her about it.

176
00:09:09,368 --> 00:09:10,487
I just finished calling her.

177
00:09:10,488 --> 00:09:11,567
She didn't answer my call.

178
00:09:11,568 --> 00:09:12,508
You should forget it.

179
00:09:36,767 --> 00:09:37,628
Xiang Nan,

180
00:09:37,687 --> 00:09:38,686
why don't you call Jiang

181
00:09:38,687 --> 00:09:39,646
again?

182
00:09:39,647 --> 00:09:41,087
I already called him. He didn't pick up.

183
00:09:41,088 --> 00:09:43,707
I already called him several times.
He didn't even reply to my texts.

184
00:09:43,927 --> 00:09:44,628
Look at you.

185
00:09:45,287 --> 00:09:48,028
Enough. You should stop forcing her.

186
00:09:48,088 --> 00:09:49,628
What? Did I do the wrong thing?

187
00:09:53,448 --> 00:09:53,967
Dad, Mom,

188
00:09:53,968 --> 00:09:55,247
why don't you guys eat first?

189
00:09:55,248 --> 00:09:55,886
It's late now.

190
00:09:55,887 --> 00:09:56,327
Precisely.

191
00:09:56,328 --> 00:09:57,748
Why don't you take a bite first?

192
00:09:57,767 --> 00:09:59,428
How could I be in the mood to eat?

193
00:09:59,488 --> 00:10:01,046
I'm just worried
that you might be hungry.

194
00:10:01,047 --> 00:10:02,447
I can hang in there
even when I'm hungry.

195
00:10:02,448 --> 00:10:04,508
All of you are doing it. Why can't I do it?

196
00:10:04,767 --> 00:10:06,587
Did everyone forget about their manners?

197
00:10:07,088 --> 00:10:07,806
Miss Xiang.

198
00:10:07,807 --> 00:10:08,567
Mr. Wang?

199
00:10:08,568 --> 00:10:09,646
This is Mr. Wang,

200
00:10:09,647 --> 00:10:11,268
Jiang's chauffeur.

201
00:10:11,568 --> 00:10:12,406
Have a seat.

202
00:10:12,407 --> 00:10:13,487
- Come inside.
- Have a seat.

203
00:10:13,488 --> 00:10:15,028
Where's Jiang? Is he at the entrance?

204
00:10:15,488 --> 00:10:16,908
Mr. Jiang is still in the meeting.

205
00:10:17,647 --> 00:10:18,587
It's like this.

206
00:10:18,848 --> 00:10:19,766
He's worried

207
00:10:19,767 --> 00:10:20,926
that you guys might wait for him

208
00:10:20,927 --> 00:10:22,347
and delay the dinner.

209
00:10:22,368 --> 00:10:23,840
That'll affect your parents' health.

210
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:26,006
Therefore, he had booked
a dinner appointment at a restaurant.

211
00:10:26,007 --> 00:10:27,320
He sent me here to pick you guys up.

212
00:10:27,328 --> 00:10:27,926
What?

213
00:10:27,927 --> 00:10:29,107
Does that mean

214
00:10:29,167 --> 00:10:30,947
all of us have to go there instead?

215
00:10:31,568 --> 00:10:32,508
Jiang Nan.

216
00:10:32,927 --> 00:10:36,247
Why don't you tell Jiang Hongbin
that we can have the meal another time.

217
00:10:36,248 --> 00:10:37,967
We can have a meal
with him when he's free.

218
00:10:37,968 --> 00:10:38,868
Don't say that.

219
00:10:39,248 --> 00:10:41,268
What are you saying?

220
00:10:41,448 --> 00:10:43,367
Xiang Nan, don't do that.

221
00:10:43,368 --> 00:10:44,067
Wait.

222
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:46,046
No matter if he's changing
the venue or the time,

223
00:10:46,047 --> 00:10:47,006
don't you think he should

224
00:10:47,007 --> 00:10:48,166
notify me in advance?

225
00:10:48,167 --> 00:10:50,107
How could he do this suddenly?

226
00:10:50,887 --> 00:10:51,947
Let me call him.

227
00:10:56,368 --> 00:10:57,868
He's not answering my calls again.

228
00:10:58,248 --> 00:10:59,827
He never answered any of them.

229
00:10:59,887 --> 00:11:01,628
Mr. Jiang has been
in a meeting all along.

230
00:11:02,968 --> 00:11:04,327
Jiang, you better call me back

231
00:11:04,328 --> 00:11:05,748
after hearing this.

232
00:11:07,128 --> 00:11:08,868
How could he act like this?

233
00:11:09,527 --> 00:11:11,067
Mr. Wang, tell him this.

234
00:11:11,608 --> 00:11:13,668
We can cancel the meal if he's busy.
Just forget about it.

235
00:11:14,208 --> 00:11:14,908
Don't do that!

236
00:11:20,088 --> 00:11:21,388
Mr. Wang, don't do that.

237
00:11:21,968 --> 00:11:23,908
Please wait for us outside, okay?

238
00:11:24,587 --> 00:11:25,926
I'll wait for you guys outside, then.

239
00:11:25,927 --> 00:11:27,227
Thank you so much.

240
00:11:28,728 --> 00:11:31,067
You don't need to wait.
Just cancel the dinner appointment.

241
00:11:31,088 --> 00:11:32,508
Girl, you...

242
00:11:32,927 --> 00:11:34,006
How could you not go there?

243
00:11:34,007 --> 00:11:35,367
You have to look at the bigger picture.

244
00:11:35,368 --> 00:11:36,487
It doesn't matter

245
00:11:36,488 --> 00:11:38,087
where your mother and I have to go,
you know?

246
00:11:38,088 --> 00:11:39,886
It doesn't matter
even if we change the venue.

247
00:11:39,887 --> 00:11:41,028
What should we do, then?

248
00:11:41,228 --> 00:11:41,886
You can't do this.

249
00:11:41,887 --> 00:11:43,686
What do you mean by it doesn't matter
even if we change the venue?

250
00:11:43,687 --> 00:11:45,200
What bigger picture
are you talking about here?

251
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:45,908
Mom, tell me.

252
00:11:46,007 --> 00:11:47,707
Isn't he considered a junior?

253
00:11:47,707 --> 00:11:49,087
What does it mean
to pay a visit in person?

254
00:11:49,088 --> 00:11:51,067
That means he has to come here
and visit us in person.

255
00:11:51,067 --> 00:11:52,567
Your mother and I
are much older than you.

256
00:11:52,568 --> 00:11:54,788
Are you teaching us what to do now?

257
00:11:55,568 --> 00:11:56,646
It's half past seven.

258
00:11:56,647 --> 00:11:58,548
Now, he wants us
to head outside for dinner?

259
00:11:58,807 --> 00:11:59,286
Listen,

260
00:11:59,287 --> 00:12:00,707
we have to attend
the dinner appointment.

261
00:12:00,848 --> 00:12:03,067
When we're there, I'll tell Jiang this,

262
00:12:03,488 --> 00:12:06,548
"You're disrespecting Xiang Nan
with your sudden arrangement, you know?"

263
00:12:07,007 --> 00:12:08,307
This is ridiculous.

264
00:12:08,527 --> 00:12:09,720
Xiang Nan, what do you think?

265
00:12:12,167 --> 00:12:13,227
But Xiang Nan,

266
00:12:13,728 --> 00:12:14,587
Xiang Qian,

267
00:12:14,687 --> 00:12:16,587
we still need to attend
the dinner appointment,

268
00:12:16,687 --> 00:12:17,467
don't you guys agree?

269
00:12:18,767 --> 00:12:20,148
Don't just sit down.

270
00:12:20,568 --> 00:12:23,788
Go and get changed. We have to go.

271
00:12:24,608 --> 00:12:26,166
Stop staring at them.

272
00:12:26,167 --> 00:12:27,607
Come on. Let's go and get changed.

273
00:12:27,608 --> 00:12:29,827
Wait here. Don't waste any time.
Get ready.

274
00:12:30,807 --> 00:12:31,748
My goodness.

275
00:12:35,007 --> 00:12:35,367
Wait.

276
00:12:35,368 --> 00:12:37,207
What's going on?

277
00:12:37,208 --> 00:12:39,406
I don't know either.
He doesn't do this usually.

278
00:12:39,407 --> 00:12:41,428
He has always been punctual.

279
00:12:49,088 --> 00:12:49,908
Over here, please.

280
00:12:51,488 --> 00:12:52,748
There's a giant lake beside it?

281
00:12:53,208 --> 00:12:54,347
- This is great.
- There's fish.

282
00:12:56,407 --> 00:12:58,187
Have you not seen a fish before?
My goodness.

283
00:12:59,448 --> 00:13:00,668
Is that a swan?

284
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:03,406
What are you doing?

285
00:13:03,407 --> 00:13:04,548
I want to take a picture of it.

286
00:13:05,488 --> 00:13:06,508
She wants to take a picture.

287
00:13:07,368 --> 00:13:08,447
Don't turn on the flashlight.

288
00:13:08,448 --> 00:13:09,748
It'll scare the swan away.

289
00:13:11,888 --> 00:13:12,987
You're doing it for real, huh?

290
00:13:13,208 --> 00:13:14,347
Mom, be careful.

291
00:13:14,767 --> 00:13:15,686
It's not afraid of humans.

292
00:13:15,687 --> 00:13:17,107
It'll hurt when it pecks you.

293
00:13:17,848 --> 00:13:18,628
Come on.

294
00:13:22,448 --> 00:13:23,947
They even have swans here?

295
00:13:29,007 --> 00:13:30,686
I think this place will look better

296
00:13:30,687 --> 00:13:31,827
during the day.

297
00:13:32,448 --> 00:13:34,668
This is a private club.

298
00:13:35,128 --> 00:13:36,646
This restaurant is hard to reserve.

299
00:13:36,647 --> 00:13:39,067
You can only get a reservation
if you make one several months in advance.

300
00:13:39,647 --> 00:13:40,668
Is that so?

301
00:13:41,728 --> 00:13:43,748
Mr. Jiang will be here
right after the meeting.

302
00:13:48,167 --> 00:13:49,788
It's not that easy

303
00:13:50,208 --> 00:13:51,908
to meet Mr. Jiang.

304
00:13:53,128 --> 00:13:54,707
Calm down.

305
00:13:55,728 --> 00:13:57,268
I'll head outside and ask him about it.

306
00:14:00,128 --> 00:14:01,307
You keep taking pictures.

307
00:14:02,608 --> 00:14:03,868
Xiang Nan is upset, you know?

308
00:14:03,887 --> 00:14:06,327
Look at the time. How can anyone
be happy without having dinner?

309
00:14:06,328 --> 00:14:07,926
You should stop
adding fuel to the flame.

310
00:14:07,927 --> 00:14:08,788
You...

311
00:14:09,167 --> 00:14:10,788
Hey, Mr. Shen.

312
00:14:11,568 --> 00:14:12,428
Miss Xiang?

313
00:14:12,968 --> 00:14:13,686
When will Mr. Jiang

314
00:14:13,687 --> 00:14:14,967
be here?

315
00:14:14,968 --> 00:14:15,447
He's coming.

316
00:14:15,448 --> 00:14:16,347
I'm going to receive him.

317
00:14:16,527 --> 00:14:17,268
Okay.

318
00:14:18,088 --> 00:14:19,107
What is this?

319
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,748
I heard that Mr. Jiang
had a heated argument

320
00:14:21,887 --> 00:14:23,207
with the other company this afternoon.

321
00:14:23,208 --> 00:14:25,028
He cut his hand as he was too agitated.

322
00:14:25,088 --> 00:14:26,908
I bought some iodine solution
and medicine for him.

323
00:14:27,488 --> 00:14:29,127
Was the injury serious?

324
00:14:29,128 --> 00:14:29,908
It's not that bad.

325
00:14:30,807 --> 00:14:32,680
Alright. What about this?
You can give them to me.

326
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:33,587
I'll hand them to him later.

327
00:14:33,728 --> 00:14:34,447
Alright.

328
00:14:34,448 --> 00:14:35,428
Okay. Thank you.

329
00:14:35,488 --> 00:14:36,307
I'll be going, then.

330
00:14:36,368 --> 00:14:37,187
You may go ahead.

331
00:14:49,287 --> 00:14:51,327
I met his secretary just now.

332
00:14:51,328 --> 00:14:52,686
He said he had arrived.

333
00:14:52,687 --> 00:14:54,548
He'll bring him inside soon.

334
00:14:57,848 --> 00:15:00,067
Look at the time. Dad and Mom
haven't had dinner yet, you know?

335
00:15:00,927 --> 00:15:02,388
I'll tell him off later.

336
00:15:02,647 --> 00:15:03,587
I'm sure he's too busy.

337
00:15:04,448 --> 00:15:05,868
Don't tell him off.

338
00:15:06,368 --> 00:15:08,028
Don't be impatient.

339
00:15:08,728 --> 00:15:10,587
He had a meeting to attend, you know?

340
00:15:11,368 --> 00:15:12,707
Guys, Mr. Jiang has arrived.

341
00:15:15,007 --> 00:15:16,166
Sorry about this.

342
00:15:16,167 --> 00:15:17,388
I had a sudden meeting just now.

343
00:15:17,527 --> 00:15:19,148
They were dragging it out.

344
00:15:21,047 --> 00:15:22,467
I'm truly sorry about this.

345
00:15:22,488 --> 00:15:23,628
This...

346
00:15:23,887 --> 00:15:26,028
They must be Mr. Xiang
and Mrs. Xiang, right?

347
00:15:27,007 --> 00:15:28,347
This is your eldest sister, right?

348
00:15:28,448 --> 00:15:29,148
That's right.

349
00:15:29,448 --> 00:15:30,347
Nice to meet you.

350
00:15:31,208 --> 00:15:32,247
Please don't stand.

351
00:15:32,248 --> 00:15:33,707
Please have a seat.

352
00:15:33,807 --> 00:15:35,166
Here, Mr. Xiang.

353
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:37,967
Mr. Jiang, we're not affecting your work
by coming here, right?

354
00:15:37,968 --> 00:15:38,567
Not at all.

355
00:15:38,568 --> 00:15:39,587
Mrs. Xiang, please.

356
00:15:39,887 --> 00:15:41,187
I'm truly sorry about this.

357
00:15:41,687 --> 00:15:42,487
You see,

358
00:15:42,488 --> 00:15:44,247
our meeting venue

359
00:15:44,248 --> 00:15:45,207
was a temporary office

360
00:15:45,208 --> 00:15:46,628
located at our site.

361
00:15:46,927 --> 00:15:48,148
The signal over there is terrible.

362
00:15:48,288 --> 00:15:50,428
I was worried that you guys
might be waiting for me for too long.

363
00:15:51,368 --> 00:15:52,967
I even texted Xiang Nan

364
00:15:52,968 --> 00:15:55,187
and said that I would
bring you guys here.

365
00:15:55,807 --> 00:15:56,526
But I only found out

366
00:15:56,527 --> 00:15:57,827
that the text wasn't delivered

367
00:15:58,047 --> 00:15:59,847
when I checked my phone
after the meeting.

368
00:15:59,848 --> 00:16:01,447
You're not a baby, you know?

369
00:16:01,448 --> 00:16:02,926
Don't you know how WeChat works?

370
00:16:02,927 --> 00:16:04,046
Don't you know how to confirm

371
00:16:04,047 --> 00:16:06,166
whether or not your texts
were delivered after sending them?

372
00:16:06,167 --> 00:16:07,646
We had to wait for you
for so long, you know?

373
00:16:07,647 --> 00:16:08,428
I know that.

374
00:16:08,887 --> 00:16:10,307
I'm truly sorry about this.

375
00:16:13,887 --> 00:16:14,628
Come in.

376
00:16:16,608 --> 00:16:17,766
I've already made the order.

377
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:18,886
We won't need to order again.

378
00:16:18,887 --> 00:16:22,308
Mr. Jiang, the Hengjiang Reeves' shad,
which you had ordered, is ready now.

379
00:16:22,308 --> 00:16:24,440
Should we prepare it according
to what you told us in the evening?

380
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:26,788
Since we have elderly customers,
we can make something blander for them.

381
00:16:26,847 --> 00:16:28,120
Steam it using the traditional method.

382
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:28,748
That'll do.

383
00:16:29,128 --> 00:16:30,827
No ginger in all of the dishes, right?

384
00:16:31,047 --> 00:16:32,187
That's right. No ginger.

385
00:16:32,927 --> 00:16:34,548
Alright. Please wait a moment.

386
00:16:35,007 --> 00:16:35,748
Hurry up.

387
00:16:39,328 --> 00:16:40,207
You have enough time

388
00:16:40,208 --> 00:16:42,046
to make arrangements with the chef,

389
00:16:42,047 --> 00:16:44,227
yet you have no time to answer my calls?

390
00:16:45,128 --> 00:16:45,926
I told Shen to make

391
00:16:45,927 --> 00:16:47,707
the arrangement in advance.

392
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:49,286
I was in a meeting the entire afternoon.

393
00:16:49,287 --> 00:16:50,788
I hardly went out at all.

394
00:16:51,007 --> 00:16:53,087
So, you know that I don't like ginger?

395
00:16:53,088 --> 00:16:55,607
Mrs. Xiang, I heard from
Xiang Nan that you didn't like ginger.

396
00:16:55,608 --> 00:16:57,686
That's why I instructed the kitchen

397
00:16:57,687 --> 00:16:58,827
to omit ginger in their dishes.

398
00:16:59,088 --> 00:17:00,166
I appreciate your effort.

399
00:17:00,167 --> 00:17:01,227
You're very thoughtful.

400
00:17:01,407 --> 00:17:02,868
It's what I should do.

401
00:17:04,407 --> 00:17:05,347
Jiang,

402
00:17:05,887 --> 00:17:06,567
although I know

403
00:17:06,568 --> 00:17:08,307
that you're super busy today,

404
00:17:08,448 --> 00:17:09,087
you did

405
00:17:09,088 --> 00:17:10,767
do the wrong thing today.

406
00:17:10,768 --> 00:17:11,767
I think you have

407
00:17:11,768 --> 00:17:13,206
to apologize to Dad,

408
00:17:13,207 --> 00:17:14,428
Mom,

409
00:17:14,568 --> 00:17:16,668
and Qian.

410
00:17:17,167 --> 00:17:18,807
Didn't Jiang explain himself just now?

411
00:17:18,808 --> 00:17:20,486
He had a meeting today.

412
00:17:20,487 --> 00:17:21,547
No, Mr. Xiang.

413
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:23,227
Xiang Nan is right.

414
00:17:23,407 --> 00:17:24,047
I was wrong today.

415
00:17:24,048 --> 00:17:26,880
It was my fault. I was worried
that you guys might wait for too long.

416
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:28,667
I didn't know what time
my meeting was going to finish.

417
00:17:28,667 --> 00:17:30,200
It takes me 40 minutes
if I rush to your house.

418
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,646
It'll make me look more disrespectful.

419
00:17:31,647 --> 00:17:33,367
Therefore, I told Xiang Nan
to bring you guys here.

420
00:17:33,368 --> 00:17:36,007
What about this?
Mr. Xiang, Mrs. Xiang, Qian,

421
00:17:36,008 --> 00:17:37,926
let's put aside the rules
this time around, okay?

422
00:17:37,927 --> 00:17:39,707
Next time,

423
00:17:39,768 --> 00:17:41,628
I'll make it up to you guys.

424
00:17:42,008 --> 00:17:42,747
Okay?

425
00:17:42,967 --> 00:17:44,428
It's fine.

426
00:17:44,967 --> 00:17:46,227
I...

427
00:17:46,247 --> 00:17:47,807
I feel like saying something.

428
00:17:47,808 --> 00:17:48,406
Please go ahead.

429
00:17:48,407 --> 00:17:49,908
Please call me Hongbin.

430
00:17:51,328 --> 00:17:53,108
This is my first time
meeting you, Jiang.

431
00:17:53,368 --> 00:17:54,588
I can tell

432
00:17:54,727 --> 00:17:57,108
that you've put in a lot of effort
for the dinner arrangement.

433
00:17:57,447 --> 00:17:58,828
You're very thoughtful as well.

434
00:17:59,447 --> 00:18:01,987
However, the way you handled this

435
00:18:02,768 --> 00:18:04,987
was kind of inappropriate.

436
00:18:05,247 --> 00:18:08,428
Let's forget about the fact
if we should be here

437
00:18:08,848 --> 00:18:09,646
or

438
00:18:09,647 --> 00:18:11,428
if you should visit us at our house.

439
00:18:11,768 --> 00:18:13,027
That's just a trivial detail.

440
00:18:13,447 --> 00:18:14,607
I don't mind

441
00:18:14,608 --> 00:18:15,747
these rules.

442
00:18:16,207 --> 00:18:17,707
What I'm concerned about

443
00:18:18,368 --> 00:18:20,747
is that you should respect

444
00:18:20,808 --> 00:18:22,787
Xiang Nan's opinion,

445
00:18:22,967 --> 00:18:23,828
am I right?

446
00:18:24,048 --> 00:18:24,707
You're right.

447
00:18:25,088 --> 00:18:27,807
I know you're busy with work
and that you can't head home in time.

448
00:18:27,808 --> 00:18:28,828
What should you do, then?

449
00:18:29,247 --> 00:18:30,787
Merely texting her on WeChat

450
00:18:31,368 --> 00:18:32,707
isn't enough, you know?

451
00:18:33,368 --> 00:18:34,388
You should've

452
00:18:35,088 --> 00:18:36,747
at least called Xiang Nan

453
00:18:37,207 --> 00:18:39,108
and discuss the situation with her.

454
00:18:39,568 --> 00:18:40,747
Mr. Xiang, you're totally right.

455
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:44,588
Xiang Nan, I've criticized Jiang.

456
00:18:45,967 --> 00:18:47,646
Stop being angry, okay?

457
00:18:47,647 --> 00:18:48,547
I'm not angry.

458
00:18:50,128 --> 00:18:50,787
Alright.

459
00:18:50,808 --> 00:18:51,588
What about this?

460
00:18:51,848 --> 00:18:54,646
I'll start by
pouring myself three drinks.

461
00:18:54,647 --> 00:18:56,507
They serve as my apology.

462
00:18:56,808 --> 00:18:57,767
Don't do that.

463
00:18:57,768 --> 00:18:59,926
Don't drink like that.
Your stomach is empty.

464
00:18:59,927 --> 00:19:01,787
Just one drink is enough.

465
00:19:01,848 --> 00:19:03,628
Alright, Mrs. Xiang.
I'll heed your advice.

466
00:19:04,808 --> 00:19:07,027
I'm truly sorry about today.

467
00:19:13,927 --> 00:19:15,507
Why isn't the cold dish ready yet?

468
00:19:16,008 --> 00:19:16,607
What about this?

469
00:19:16,608 --> 00:19:18,507
I'll head to the kitchen and urge them.

470
00:19:18,647 --> 00:19:19,246
Xiang Nan,

471
00:19:19,247 --> 00:19:20,707
you can chat with your parents.

472
00:19:25,568 --> 00:19:26,127
Enough already.

473
00:19:26,128 --> 00:19:27,567
He said that he was in a meeting.

474
00:19:27,568 --> 00:19:29,227
You should stop being angry at him.

475
00:19:30,288 --> 00:19:30,807
Dad.

476
00:19:30,808 --> 00:19:32,187
Dad, what's wrong with you?

477
00:19:32,528 --> 00:19:33,886
What's wrong with you today?

478
00:19:33,887 --> 00:19:35,628
How could you be
so lacking in principles?

479
00:19:35,647 --> 00:19:39,267
If he wants to pay a visit in person,
he should visit our house personally.

480
00:19:39,288 --> 00:19:39,726
Indeed.

481
00:19:39,727 --> 00:19:42,868
It's fine if he's not coming.
But he had to bring us here at this late hour.

482
00:19:42,927 --> 00:19:43,847
This is our first meeting.

483
00:19:43,848 --> 00:19:46,567
Do you expect me
to express my stand immediately?

484
00:19:46,568 --> 00:19:48,527
My tummy was growling just now.

485
00:19:48,528 --> 00:19:50,108
He didn't hear it, did he?

486
00:19:53,927 --> 00:19:55,348
I did.

487
00:19:55,568 --> 00:19:57,726
I thought the fish in the pond
was beckoning me.

488
00:19:57,727 --> 00:19:59,507
How dare you laugh?
Mom is starving because of you.

489
00:19:59,887 --> 00:20:00,726
Guys, lower your volume.

490
00:20:00,727 --> 00:20:02,148
He might hear us.

491
00:20:03,407 --> 00:20:05,428
What's wrong? Are you hungry?

492
00:20:05,528 --> 00:20:07,267
Look at the time.
How could we not be hungry?

493
00:20:07,848 --> 00:20:08,886
Dinner will be ready soon.

494
00:20:08,887 --> 00:20:10,227
We'll have a feast later.

495
00:20:25,768 --> 00:20:26,668
Mr. Xiang, Mrs. Xiang,

496
00:20:27,768 --> 00:20:29,828
I have something to say.

497
00:20:33,487 --> 00:20:35,166
Mr. Xiang, Mrs. Xiang, Qian,

498
00:20:35,167 --> 00:20:38,068
today, I wish to express my stand

499
00:20:38,088 --> 00:20:39,308
in front of you guys.

500
00:20:39,407 --> 00:20:42,148
I assume Xiang Nan has
told you guys about my situation.

501
00:20:42,288 --> 00:20:43,446
I'm usually

502
00:20:43,447 --> 00:20:44,987
busy with work.

503
00:20:45,008 --> 00:20:47,707
It might be difficult for me
to consider Xiang Nan's feelings all the time.

504
00:20:48,048 --> 00:20:49,127
But I'll definitely do my best

505
00:20:49,128 --> 00:20:50,868
to look after Xiang Nan.

506
00:20:51,927 --> 00:20:53,027
And,

507
00:20:53,647 --> 00:20:54,726
Mr. Xiang, Mrs. Xiang,

508
00:20:54,727 --> 00:20:55,747
if you guys

509
00:20:56,128 --> 00:20:57,148
don't mind,

510
00:20:57,608 --> 00:21:00,588
I would like to look after Xiang Nan
for the rest of my life.

511
00:21:10,088 --> 00:21:10,947
Mr. Jiang.

512
00:21:12,407 --> 00:21:13,486
Xiang Nan

513
00:21:13,487 --> 00:21:15,828
didn't tell us
that she was in a relationship.

514
00:21:16,247 --> 00:21:17,087
The news

515
00:21:17,088 --> 00:21:18,547
was pretty sudden for us.

516
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:20,807
And, this is our first meeting.

517
00:21:20,808 --> 00:21:21,828
Let's drop

518
00:21:22,328 --> 00:21:24,068
the serious topic, okay?

519
00:21:26,808 --> 00:21:30,507
I don't drink. I'll offer you
a toast with water.

520
00:21:30,887 --> 00:21:32,828
Alright, Qian. I'll heed your advice.

521
00:21:33,088 --> 00:21:34,588
Here, let's have a toast.

522
00:21:50,328 --> 00:21:51,348
Let me see.

523
00:21:52,328 --> 00:21:53,588
Does it hurt?

524
00:21:53,608 --> 00:21:55,406
I'm fine. Stop fiddling with it.

525
00:21:55,407 --> 00:21:56,868
Let me see.

526
00:21:57,288 --> 00:21:58,166
Xiang Nan, I'm fine.

527
00:21:58,167 --> 00:21:59,348
It's much better now.

528
00:21:59,687 --> 00:22:01,148
Was it serious?

529
00:22:02,288 --> 00:22:03,507
Did it hurt?

530
00:22:03,768 --> 00:22:04,486
I'm fine.

531
00:22:04,487 --> 00:22:06,267
I'm fine now. I'm serious.

532
00:22:07,608 --> 00:22:08,987
Alright, let's drop the topic.

533
00:22:09,687 --> 00:22:12,108
How could you be so careless?

534
00:22:16,407 --> 00:22:17,428
Jiang.

535
00:22:19,128 --> 00:22:21,187
That's how my father is.

536
00:22:21,288 --> 00:22:22,367
When he's drunk,

537
00:22:22,368 --> 00:22:24,668
he addresses everyone as his buddies.

538
00:22:25,528 --> 00:22:27,108
Your father can really
hold his liquor well.

539
00:22:27,967 --> 00:22:30,507
Even so, you shouldn't think
that he's easy to get along with.

540
00:22:31,368 --> 00:22:32,588
Is he hard to get along with?

541
00:22:33,568 --> 00:22:35,868
After all,
I'm the youngest child in the family.

542
00:22:36,167 --> 00:22:37,947
Everyone in the family dotes on me.

543
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:40,308
They're afraid
